        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Iran enters the Syrian frontline</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Syrian and Russian airstrikes have intensified in response to significant gains by the opposition, particularly in Idlib and Aleppo. In response, Iran-backed militias are <a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/syria-civil-war-rebels-aleppo-iran-bashar-assad-offensive-airport-hama-rcna182325" target="_blank">reinforcing</a> the Syrian military frontline in the north. Meanwhile, Iran and Russia remain committed to supporting Assad as Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian pledged to provide all support to the Syrian government to push back the rebels.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The coalition led by Hayat Tahrir al-Sham (HTS) has advanced but faced slowdowns due to rising diplomatic efforts. The opposition is still pushing into <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Hama,+Syria/@35.1382957,36.733561,14z/data=!4m12!1m5!3m4!2zMzXCsDA4JzAwLjAiTiAzNsKwNDUnMDAuMCJF!8m2!3d35.133333!4d36.75!3m5!1s0x1524828fcdd5b865:0x62d43f56ee62b5ef!8m2!3d35.140802!4d36.7553365!16zL20vMDJrbWp2?hl=en&entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI0MTEyNC4xIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D" target="_blank">Hama</a> and has gained control of Tel Rifaat, with calls for humanitarian corridors. Opposition leader Hadi al-Bahri stated their readiness to negotiate but insisted on continuing the fight for a political transition. <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/syria-us-germany-france-uk-call-for-de-escalation/a-70933512" target="_blank">NATO countries</a> have called for de-escalation and civilian protection, emphasizing a Syrian-led political solution per UN Security Council Resolution 2254.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>

