          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇸🇳 Senegal:</strong>    
          Senegal commemorated the <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/africa/20241201-senegal-demands-truth-80-years-french-colonial-massacre-thiaroye-france" target="_blank">80th anniversary</a> of the Thiaroye Massacre, where French colonial forces killed African soldiers in 1944 for demanding fair wages after serving in World War II. President Bassirou Diomaye Faye and France’s foreign affairs minister attended the ceremony as Senegal renewed calls for an apology and investigation. French President Emmanuel Macron admitted French responsibility in a letter calling the event a “massacre.”</p>
        </mj-text>
