          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇦🇴 Angola:</strong>   
          President Joe Biden will visit Angola on Monday, focusing on <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/01/politics/biden-promise-visit-africa/index.html" target="_blank">U.S. investment</a> in Africa amid growing Chinese and Russian influence. The trip will highlight the U.S.-backed <a href="https://www.msn.com/en-in/news/world/what-is-lobito-railway-project-biden-s-counter-to-china-s-belt-and-roads-initiative-will-trump-support-it/ar-AA1v7Fyw#:~:text=The%20Lobito%20Corridor%2C%20a%20railway%20project%20linking%20Angola%2C,promises%20to%20boost%20regional%20trade%20and%20create%20jobs." target="_blank">Lobito Corridor railway project</a>, which aims to counter China’s Belt and Road Initiative while promoting higher standards in development. Biden will meet Angolan President João Lourenço and visit key sites, including the National Slavery Museum and Lobito Port. This marks the first U.S. presidential trip to sub-Saharan Africa since 2015.</p>
        </mj-text>
